{"actual_usd":0.12470500000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":213,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24302,"reply":"\"I don't think I'd call that enough, no.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry seam of clay on my apron, looking at you plainly while the morning light shifts across the floorboards.* \"If Christ did not truly rise, then we're not being handed hope so much as a lovely lantern with no flame in it.\"\n\n*I let that sit a beat, not trying to crowd you.* \"Mind, I understand the pull of wanting the meaning without the stumbling block. But a thing like resurrection only carries the weight it promises if it happened in the flesh. Otherwise it's a poem about new beginnings—and poems can comfort, sure—but they can't rob death of its teeth.\"\n\n\"I'm not saying you have to pretend belief you don't have.\" *I lift one shoulder.* \"Better an honest, 'I can't yet,' than dressing doubt up as settled peace. But I wouldn't gut the claim and keep calling the body alive. What is it, exactly, that catches in your throat—the miracle itself, or the thought of staking yourself on something that wild?\"","rolling_24h_usd":88.06532,"run_id":"6ea57da2-9f58-477f-ab57-3ad4264f0b27"}
